    \item Embed co-creative elements (\textit{“start with why”} reflections)
    \item Draft \textbf{Operational Plan} \& \textbf{Portfolio Strategy}
\end{itemize}
\\
\textbf{Phase 3: Portfolio Mgmt. \& Incubation Toolkit}
\newline (Outputs due Apr 22 \& May 14, 2025) 
& Apr 1 -- May 14, 2025 & 
\begin{itemize}
    \item Develop portfolio management framework
    \item Create guidelines for mentorship, peer support, possible AI/green modules
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Outputs}: Portfolio Management Framework, Incubation Toolkit.
\\
\textbf{Phase 4: Follow-On Funding Strategy} 
\newline (Due Jun 12, 2025) 
& May 15 -- Jun 12, 2025 & 
\begin{itemize}
    \item Funder mapping
    \item Curated networking \& philanthropic outreach
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}: Follow-On Funding Strategy.
\\
\textbf{Phase 5: Egypt CO Model Enhancement} 
\newline (Due Jul 10, 2025) 
& Jun 13 -- Jul 10, 2025 & 
\begin{itemize}
    \item Align with imaGen/ROTA frameworks
    \item Gather local feedback \& finalize recommendations
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}: Technical Report on Localized CO Model.
\\
\textbf{Phase 6: Knowledge Products \& Technical Proposals}
\newline (Due Aug 28 \& Sep 19, 2025) 
& Jul 11 -- Sep 19, 2025 & 
\begin{itemize}
    \item Develop two knowledge products (case studies, briefs)
    \item Draft up to three technical proposals for funding
\end{itemize}
\\
\textbf{Phase 7: Capacity Building \& Webinars} 
\newline (Due Oct 24 \& Nov 18, 2025) 
& Sep 20 -- Nov 18, 2025 & 
\begin{itemize}
    \item Four capacity-building sessions (youth-led if possible)
    \item Three webinars on resilience, green/AI skills, or funding
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Outputs}: Session Reports, Webinar Documentation.
\\
\textbf{Phase 8: Results Framework}
\newline (Due Dec 31, 2025) 
& Nov 19 -- Dec 31, 2025 & 
\begin{itemize}
    \item Establish indicators, finalize data collection templates
    \item Integrate lessons learned
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}: Results Framework Document.
\\
\textbf{Ongoing Coordination \& Feedback}
& Throughout 
& 
\begin{itemize}
    \item Regular check-ins, iterative updates, stakeholder consultations
    \item Risk mitigation \& adaptation to evolving needs
\end{itemize}
\\
\bottomrule
\end{longtable}

\subsection*{2.3 Implementation Principles}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Youth Agency \& Co-Creation}: Encourage storytelling, “start with why” reflections, and peer-based idea exchange.
    \item \textbf{Flexible Thematic Alignment}: Integrate green skills, MSMEs, AI, and optional badge systems for skill recognition.
    \item \textbf{Community-Building \& Sustainability}: Use leaderboards, digital spotlights, or other incentives to maintain engagement.
    \item \textbf{Synergy with Existing Frameworks}: Reference imaGen Ventures and ROTA/Silatech for local adaptations without fixed obligations.
    \item \textbf{Incremental Adoption \& Adaptation}: Remain open to new insights, requests, or shifts in GenU’s priorities.
\end{itemize}

\section*{2.4 Next Steps}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Contract \& Kick-Off}: Upon final agreement, we can begin Phase 1 tasks by January 10, 2025.
    \item \textbf{Regular Checkpoints}: Monthly or biweekly updates ensure alignment with evolving requirements.
    \item \textbf{Refinement}: All phases remain provisional until further input from GenU stakeholders, local offices, and youth.
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Conclusion}: This plan balances clear deliverables and timelines with the flexibility to adapt to GenU’s evolving needs. Our financial proposal outlines all fees and potential travel costs, while the provisional project plan details how we will center youth, community, and innovative thematic pathways to drive impactful entrepreneurship outcomes.

\end{document}
